	('greetingsWizardDescriptionEarth', 'Alb.GreetingsWizard.Description.Earth', 'The earth line is very versatile. It offers damage over time spells (DOT\'s). It also offers area effect root, an Area effect damage and snare spell line, and a ground targeted area damage spell. It also offers the ability to nearsight players. A player who is nearsight can no longer cast from the maximum range of their spells. What else can I tell you about? [Fire], [Earth], [Ice] or are you [done].', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Constantine\'s Sound Quests', NULL),
	('greetingsWizardDescriptionFire', 'Alb.GreetingsWizard.Description.Fire', 'The fire line for a wizard offers an additional bolt, and high direct damage spells. This line also contains area effect damage spells. What else can I tell you about? [Fire], [Earth], [Ice] or are you [done].', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Constantine\'s Sound Quests', NULL),
	('greetingsWizardDescriptionIce', 'Alb.GreetingsWizard.Description.Ice', 'Training the ice line will open up a point blank area damage spell. These damage spells are far superior than any spell a wizard has in damage, but lose distance. You must be nearly on top of an enemy for him to be effected by this type of spell. Ice also offers direct damage and snare spells as well as a debuff list. What else can I tell you about? [Fire], [Earth], [Ice] or are you [done].', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Constantine\'s Sound Quests', NULL),
